2. Is it 𝗺𝗮𝗻𝗱𝗮𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘆 to have 𝗽𝗵𝘆𝘀𝗶𝗰𝗮𝗹 𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗲𝗿. What kind of 𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗲𝗿 that you really like 𝗶𝗻𝗳𝗿𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗿𝘂𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 must have
   my project infra is built in aws cloud using terraform. we use on-premise datacenters for maintaining  cassandra/ postgres db.
3. How are we going to install our 𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻. What are the 𝗮𝗿𝗰𝗵𝗶𝘁𝗲𝗰𝘁𝘂𝗿𝗲 that you are 𝗮𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗲 𝗮𝗯𝗼𝘂𝘁.
   our project designed and implmented based on microservice architecture.we have created CI/CD pipeline to compile, build,execute unit testcases, generate code quality repot using sonarqube, create docker image, deploy. as soon as PR gets approved. this build process gets triggered.
   after docker image generated, scrum teams use gitops to deploy service in cluster.
4. Are you aware about 𝗗𝗼𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗿 and 𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗲𝘀.
	docker is used for containerizing our application (example backend service) with the help of dockerfile.
	k8s is meant for orchestration purpose like autoscaling, health check. we use deployment files to configure the image and resources allocated to run the image as container like cpu,memory.
5. Why do we need 𝗗𝗼𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗿
   in the era microservice architecture, unlike monolithic, entire project is divided into multiple small services. to run this services, we dont need heavy infrastructure and  with docker, we dont need bother about os, installing application runtime install on the server.
   when we build docker image, we ensure that everything is required to run the application is included as part of it using dockerfile.
   so, docker container runs/responds/behaves similar way irrespective of environment where you run lower environment/testing/ production.
6. What is 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗿?
   container is mini server conatins all the softwares/runtimes(os,java,python,nodejs) required to run our application
7. The thing I talked about 𝗮𝗽𝗽𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻. That could be 𝗶𝗻𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗹𝗹𝗲𝗱 as a 𝗺𝗶𝗰𝗿𝗼𝘀𝗲𝗿𝘃𝗶𝗰𝗲. Can I directly put it in the 𝗱𝗼𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗿 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗿?
   first built docker image by specifying os and applcation runtime and compiled files and configuration files to be copied in specific structure.
   then using k8s, we run the image as container.
8. Uses of 𝗞𝘂𝗯𝗲𝗿𝗻𝗲𝘁𝗲𝘀 over 𝗱𝗼𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗿 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘁𝗮𝗶𝗻𝗲𝗿?
   k8s is an orchestration tool. it has features that helps to autoscale our services based on load, rolling update new version of the service.
   on peak black friday, based on the load ( mostly cpu), instances should be created automatically. we can acheive this out of box using k8s horizontal scaling.
